## **Notes**

### JavaScript Variables

- Decleration + Assignment
- Conventions: camelCase
- const vs let
  - const = constant, not reassignable
  - let = can be reassigned

```js
let locationOfPerson = "Boston";
```

### Data Types

- Strings
- Integers
- Float

### Arithmetic

- modulus %
- add +, subtract -, multiply \*, divide /

### Common functions

```js
document.getElementById('id').onclick = myFunc

function myFunc() {
    document.querySelector('body').style.backgroundColor = 'rgba(241,63,247,1)
    document.querySelector('body').style.color = 'white'
}
```

### Operators

== equal to
=== equal to (value + type)

!= not equal
!=== not equal to (value + type)

> greater than
> < less than
> = greathen than or equal
> <= less than or equal

&& and
|| or

### Conditionals

if(condition is true) {
//do funcs
}else if(condition is true) {
//do other funcs
}else{
//do this func
}
